Financial Assets
Overview



OVERVIEW
Garrison's Financial Assets Group acquires, finances, and originates portfolios of consumer and commercial assets. The Financial Assets Group invests in portfolios of both performing and non-performing loans as well as hard assets which are conducive to generating quantifiable, predictable cashflow streams. Representative asset types include:

commercial and industrial loans, 
student loans, 
auto loans, 
consumer unsecured loans, 
recreational vehicle loans, 
home improvement loans, 
equipment leases, 
aircraft leases,
shipping assets,
rail assets, and 
other asset types 





