August 4, 2015
Glenn Atkins
Family Office


 
Family Services Office
This specialized division within Garrison Financial focuses on the ultra affluent market. We provide comprehensive and flexible solutions to the issues that are unique to your family’s needs. With extensive experience in servicing investors and their family offices, we combine technology and institutional capabilities with a tradition of personalized service to meet our clients’ complex financial needs.
We have experience working with families who implement sophisticated investment programs, require consolidated reporting, and want exposure to best practices employed by other successful families and family offices.You will receive the highest level of client service and relationship management backed by expert wealth planning and financial management strategists. In addition, we utilize the strength of an industry leading custody platform.
You will also be provided with industry leading technology and reporting capabilities. Our exceptional asset management capabilities include customized tax-managed equity, enhanced cash and tax-exempt fixed-income portfolios. Our significant experience and intellectual capital will help generations of families build and preserve great wealth. 
 
 Darrick Bradley, MBA – Chief Operating Officer *protected email* Mr. Bradley earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration from the University of Arkansas. He also holds a Master of Business Administration from Webster University in St. Louis, MO. Mr. Bradley has extensive experience in business development and operations management. Mr. Bradley joined Garrison Financial in 2007 as Vice President of Family Office Services. He was promoted to Chief Operating Officer for Garrison Financial in 2009. Prior to joining Garrison Financial, Mr. Bradley acquired management operation experience working for Burlington Northern Santa Fe Corporation.
 
Courtney Madden Ogden – Vice President, Family Office Services *protected email* Ms. Ogden received a BSBA in accounting from Sam M. Walton College of Business at the University of Arkansas. In her current role as Vice President of Family Office Services at Garrison Financial, Ms. Ogden helps organize the administration of investments as well as finances, to include insurance, budgeting, family-owned business, charitable giving, tax services, and wealth transfer, making Garrison Financial Corporation stand out from conventional family offices. Ms. Ogden also oversees financial and cost accounting, payroll, accounts payable, accounts receivable, and cash management for individuals, fiduciaries, and various business entities. Ms. Ogden also serves on the Fayetteville Chamber of Commerce Board of Directors and is an active member of the Northwest Arkansas Community.

