Quarterly Market Letter – 3Q 2015Uncertainty about Fed policy, woes in China, and sliding commodity prices weighed heavily on the equity markets in the third quarter, bringing about the long awaited correction that had eluded stocks for almost 4 years.  Global growth concerns took center stage as China’s economy continues to slow.  The Chinese government took the markets by surprise[…]
Market Wrap September 2015The markets continued their downward trajectory during September with the S&P 500 Index registering a return of -2.64%, bringing the year to date decline to negative -6.74%.  For the trailing 12 months, the S&P 500 is down -2.65%. Year-over-year, crude oil is down from about $95.00/bbl to ~ $45.00/bbl, or a decline of almost 53%[…]


